cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of single image haze removal, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deep learning model for haze removal, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for haze removal, which is a popular topic in the field of artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category. The paper also involves the use of optimization techniques for improving the aesthetic quality of the haze-free image, which falls under the category of graphics. Hence, cs.GR (Computer Graphics) is also a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed model on synthetic as well as real-world datasets, which falls under the category of multimedia. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category.
